<TITLE>
Open source resources on Verilog
</TITLE>

<CONTENT>
<div>Followings are two prominent simulators available as open-source.&nbsp;
<ul>
	<li> Icarus -<a href="http://icarus.com/eda/verilog/"> http://icarus.com/eda/verilog/</a></li>
	<li> Verilator - <a href="http://www.veripool.org/wiki/verilator">http://www.veripool.org/wiki/verilator</a></li>
</ul>
</div>
<div></div>
<div>Icarus  is still being developed but it can be used for advanced assignments. I am not sure whether it support full 'synthesis-able subset' of Verilog.  Verilator is more advanced (to my knowledge), it can easily be  integrated with C++/SystemC/Matlab.</div>
<div>Have a look at this crazy place also <a href="http://www.opencollector.org/">http://www.opencollector.org/</a></div>
